Black Ownership of South Africa’s Mining Industry at 28%, Chamber Says

-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 
2011-08-24T07:35:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-24/black-ownership-of-south-africa-s-mining-industry-at-28-chamber-says.html
The weighted average of black
ownership of  South Africa ’s mining industry is 28 percent, the
Chamber of Mines said in a written presentation to the country’s
lawmakers in  Cape Town  today.  At least 28.6 percent of top managers in mining are black
while 36.8 percent of middle management are black, the Chamber
of Mines said, using data compiled from its members.
Parliament’s mineral resources committee is holding hearings on
the mining charter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mike Cohen in Cape Town at 
